# UI Style + Code Quality Rule

Applies to **every UI change**. If you touch UI code, satisfy all sections below.

---

## 0) Golden Rules
- **Mobile-first**: small screens first, enhance at `md+`.
- **Consistency > novelty**: reuse existing patterns/components.
- **No one-off styling**: no arbitrary values or bespoke variants.
- **Complete experiences**: loading/empty/error/success/disabled states required.
- **Accessible by default**: semantic HTML + keyboard + focus management.
- **Brand design system**: see `design-system.mdc` for brand colors, Fustat typography, Tag rules.

---

## 1) Spacing (4pt grid only)
All spacing must be multiples of 4: `4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64…`

Scale: `4`=micro, `8`=small, `12`=compact, `16`=default, `24`=section, `32`=major section, `48+`=hero.

Defaults: page padding `16px`/`24px` (mobile/desktop), card `p-16`/`p-24`, stacks `gap-8`–`gap-24`, forms label→input `gap-8`, group→group `gap-16`.

### Page Container (MANDATORY)
Use `PageContainer` from `@/components/ui/PageContainer` or the standard CSS pattern with variables:
- `--page-max-width: 1200px`, `--page-max-width-narrow: 800px`
- `--page-padding-mobile: 16px`, `--page-padding-desktop: 24px`

Never hardcode max-width/padding. One container per page (no nesting).
Reference pages: `/subscriber-insights`, `/videos`, `/competitors`.

---

## 2) Typography
- 1–2 font families max. Clean sans-serif for UI.
- Hierarchy: H1 (page title) → H2 (sections) → H3 (sub-sections/cards) → Body → Muted/Meta → Label.
- Readable on mobile. Use size/weight + spacing for hierarchy, not color alone.

---

## 3) Visual Hierarchy
Every screen must answer: **What is this?** → **What can I do?** → **What matters most?**
- More space around important elements. Related items close, unrelated items separated.
- Section pattern: title → description (optional) → content → action.

---

## 4) Alignment & Layout
- Align to a clear grid. Left-align dense content. Center only for small hero/empty states.
- No fixed widths — use max-width containers and responsive layouts.

---

## 5) Components & Design System
- Search for existing components before creating new ones.
- Use design tokens/utility scale — no inline magic numbers.
- Use **variants** (intent/size/tone), not copy-paste class piles.
- Reusable components: clear props, sane defaults, minimal API surface.

---

## 6) Accessibility
- Semantic elements: `button` (actions), `a` (navigation), `nav`, `main`, `header`, `section`, `label`.
- Keyboard: all interactive elements Tab-reachable, visible focus, visual tab order.
- Forms: every input has a label, use `aria-invalid`/`aria-describedby` for errors. Don't clear input on validation failure.
- Dialogs: accessible title, focus trap, ESC closes, return focus on close.
- Sufficient contrast. Don't rely on color alone (include icon/text/shape).

---

## 7) Interaction States
For every interactive/async surface, implement:
- **Loading**: skeleton/spinner + disable actions
- **Empty**: explain why + next step
- **Error**: actionable message + retry
- **Success**: confirmation when meaningful
- **Disabled**: clear reason (tooltip/help text)

---

## 8) Mobile-first
- Start single-column; add columns at `md+`.
- Comfortable tap targets. No tiny hit areas. No horizontal scroll.

---

## 9) Performance
- Server Components by default. Avoid unnecessary re-renders.
- Virtualize large lists. Optimized images with dimensions. Avoid heavy client libraries.

---

## 10) Definition of Done
- [ ] Spacing: multiples of 4
- [ ] Hierarchy: title → sections → actions
- [ ] Typography consistent, readable on mobile
- [ ] Alignment clean
- [ ] All interaction states implemented
- [ ] Accessible (labels, focus, keyboard, contrast)
- [ ] No one-off values; tokens/variants used
- [ ] No emojis

Rule exceptions only for design token constraints or platform-native behavior — leave a comment explaining why.
